Notions of a crawler &#39;status&#39; and crawl job completion status need some
work.

See CrawlJobHandler#loadJobs and the state.job file in each crawl job
directory for examples of finding finished job status.

On control and &#39;status&#39; of a currently running job, in HEAD, the
pausing, stopping, stop, control mechanism will probably change -- It
has already (The stopping currently doesn&#39;t work) -- with a &#39;status&#39;
getting mechanism in accordance. The eventing needs to change so its
more robust. We&#39;re seeing conditions where crawler disregards calls to
pause and stop. We&#39;d like to make status and eventing available via JMX.

